<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-10-09.S3W-27114.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa1009.htm#8">Scottish Government</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-10-09.S3W-27114.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80312" speakername="George Foulkes (Lothians) (Lab)" spid="S3W-27114" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa1009.htm#8" holdingdate="2009-09-23">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what actions of the Scottish Government require parliamentary approval.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-10-09.S3W-27114.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80300" speakername="Bruce Crawford" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa1009.htm#8">

  <p>Ministers are accountable to the parliament for the exercise of the powers, duties and functions conferred on them by statute, convention and under the royal prerogative.</p>

